Rating: 4
A simple and delicious recipe that can be made during the week. I made some minor changes to help clean out the fridge. I only used 1 cup of panko, chopped seeded jalapeno, bag of spinach and chopped and sauted an onion along with the mushroom stems and added to the mixture. I used feta and parm versus mozz just cause that's what I had on hand. Enjoy!

Rating: 3
I really liked this recipe. I took the advice of a previous reviewer and added zucchini. It tasted good, but it made my panko soggy so I was missing that crunch. I added the sun dried tomatoes and those are keepers. I also chopped up the stems and added them to the stuffing. I'll definitely make again and even experiment with other stuffing items. I really don't think you can go wrong with this recipe. it's a great base.

