Rating: 3
Am not sure what flavor was missing for the person who said it was tasteless! Perhaps they forgot to add something. Anyway, followed suggestion of another about adding salt and pepper. Next time I will probably just add pepper because of the salt in the butter. Recipe didn't say, but I did them on medium heat on gas grill (I love my Weber Baby Q). Didn't have any fresh Parm on hand so used pre-grated combo of Parm, Romano and Asiago which probably kicked up the flavor some. I made half the recipe using enormous mushrooms, but had quite a bit of filling left over. Made it with grilled bourbon glazed salmon (took the shrooms off, turned heat to high for a minute, put salmon on for 3 minutes, turning at halftime) and a simple salad with roquefort dressing but could see a good cole slaw (which, in my book means a dressing of mayo and a good splash of lemon) going well with it, instead.

Rating: 4
